HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 578
By Raper
A RESOLUTION to honor and congratulate Kimora Fields of
Bradley Central High School upon her
remarkable success as an athlete and student.
WHEREAS, we are pleased to recognize and commend those successful high school
students who, through their magnificent exploits, bring honor to Tennessee and serve as
exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable individual is Kimora Fields of Bradley Central High
School, an athlete of extraordinary talent, skill, and dedication, who not only has proven herself
a formidable competitor on the basketball court but a distinguished student and community
leader as well; and
WHEREAS, as a three-year starter with the Bradley Central Bearettes, Ms. Fields has
proven her leadership skills as an underclassman through her ability to inspire her teammates,
showing them not only how to excel on the court but also how to represent their school and
community with dignity; and
WHEREAS, during her time with the Bradley Central Bearettes, Kimora Fields has
scored a total of 2,055 career points and has been the recipient of a number of noteworthy
honors, including the Basketball Coaches Association of Tennessee 4A Player of the Year and
MaxPreps Tennessee Player of the Year awards; and
WHEREAS, ranked number thirty-two on the ESPN Super 60 list, Ms. Fields was named
a MaxPreps Freshman All-American and Sophomore All-American, twice named to the
Tennessee Sports Writers All-State team, and twice named a Tennessee Secondary School
Athletic Association (TSSAA) State Tournament MVP; and
