WHEREAS, Ms. Fields has led the Bradley Central Bearettes to three TSSAA State
Championship titles, and in 2024, she set the TSSAA season record for individual field goals at
69.2 percent; and
WHEREAS, more recently, Kimora Fields was awarded the prestigious TSSAA 4A Miss
Basketball award, the highest individual accolade in the State, which duly recognizes her
dedication and exceptional skill as an athlete; and
WHEREAS, her athletic achievements aside, Ms. Fields has earned an exemplary grade
point average of 4.0 while participating in numerous extracurricular activities, including National
Honor Society, Beta Club, and Student Council; additionally, she is involved in HOSA, ATS the
Bridge, and Link Crew, demonstrating her commitment to personal growth, peer mentorship,
and serving others; and
WHEREAS, a leader in her community, Kimora Fields has devoted her time and talents
to a number of local causes and organizations, such as the Empty Stocking Fund, the Lynn
Jones Thanksgiving Food Drive, the Bee Kind event, the Salvation Army Homeless Shelter, the
elementary school basketball Play Day, and elementary school fall festivals; and
WHEREAS, Kimora Fields epitomizes all that is good in today's student athlete, as she
has achieved a high level of success in sports while evincing great character both on and off the
court; and
WHEREAS, Ms. Fields's notable achievements are a source of great pride for her family,
her coaches, her community, and her school, and it is appropriate that we recognize this
accomplished athlete and student; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Kimora Fields of Bradley Central High School
